"Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gresham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lincolnshire): habitational name from a place in Norfolk, so named from Old English <i>græs</i>, <i>gærs</i> ‘grass(land), pasturage’ + <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’ or <i>hamm</i> ‘enclosure hemmed in by water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Grisham","meanings":["English: variant of   Gresham  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":12,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":21,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Gresham was born in 1316, in Holt, Norfolk, England. She married Sir Edward De Gresham Knight in 1336, in Holt, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1377, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1316–1377":"1316–1377","1312–1377":"1312–1377","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1366–1400":"1366–1400","–Male":"Surnud","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1348":"1348","1336":"1336","1400":"1400","1312":"1312","1366":"1366","1377":"1377","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","6 May 1348":"6. mai 1348","1328":"1328","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England":"Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Holt, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1316–1377":"1316–1377","1312–1377":"1312–1377","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1366–1400":"1366–1400","–Male":"Kuollut","1316":"1316","1337":"1337","1348":"1348","1336":"1336","1400":"1400","1312":"1312","1366":"1366","1377":"1377","1410":"1410","1453":"1453","6 May 1348":"6. toukokuuta 1348","1328":"1328","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, England":"Milton Keynes, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Holt, Norfolk, England":"Holt, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1316–1377":"1316–1377","1312–1377":"1312–1377","1348–1410":"1348–1410","1366–1400":"1366–1400",